I\\\\u{2019}m seeking support for travel expenses, including airfare and accommodation, for my stay in Bangkok from November 8 to April 11. Any assistance or recommendations for affordable lodging options would be greatly appreciated. \\\\nThank you.", "category": "Events & Hackathons", "timeline": {"status": "DRAFT"}, "supervisor": null, "description": "### **Introduction**\\\\n\\\\n[Nearstack](https://www.nearstack.weminal.com/) focuses on simplifying frontend development for Web3 by utilizing NEAR BOS components, enhanced by AI-generated code suggestions. We have created a platform that allows developers to visualize component relationships through a React flow interface. This approach makes it easier to understand how different components interact, improving developer efficiency and contributing to the growing NEAR ecosystem.\\\\n\\\\n### **Purpose**\\\\n\\\\nWe are passionate about advancing our project and making a meaningful contribution to the NEAR ecosystem. We see a lot of potential in our platform to create real-world value by streamlining development processes with AI and BOS components. The Bangkok hackathon offers an incredible opportunity for us to take this project further, engage with like-minded developers, and learn from the NEAR community. Attending the event will help us refine our vision and push the boundaries of what\\\\\\'s possible with our project.\\\\n\\\\n### **Request for Travel Stipend**\\\\n\\\\nWe are seeking assistance with flights to Bangkok, which cost approximately $350 per person. We would also greatly appreciate staying at a NEAR Hackerhouse if available. If not, we request up to $200 per person for accommodation. We are not requesting any additional funds for food or miscellaneous expenses, as we plan to cover those ourselves.\\\\n\\\\nDeparture: Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam \\\\u{2192} Bangkok, Thailand\\\\n\\\\nReturn: Bangkok, Thailand \\\\u{2192} Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam\\\\n\\\\n### **Estimated breakdown:**\\\\n\\\\n- Flight cost per person: $350\\\\n- Accommodation cost per person: $200\\\\n- Team size: 5 students\\\\n- Request per student: $500 (Capping according to T&C)\\\\n- Total 5 * 500: $2500 (We can pay $1500 ourselves)\\\\n- Total request: $1000\\\\n\\\\n### **About Our Project: Frontend Flow with NEAR BOS and AI**\\\\n\\\\nOur project integrates NEAR BOS components with AI-driven code suggestions to simplify the frontend development process. We provide a visual React flow interface, allowing developers to see how components interact. This approach enhances the efficiency and clarity of development workflows, particularly within decentralized applications. By contributing to the NEAR ecosystem, we aim to make Web3 development more accessible to all.\\\\nExplore ours project apply to REDACTED Bangkok: https://www.nearstack.weminal.com/\\\\n\\\\n### Past Project\\\\nWedata - 3RD Native track at Web3Hackfest: https://devfolio.co/projects/wedata-3418\\\\nFastUI - Fast component UI on BOS at BOS hacks: https://near.social/fastui.near/widget/FastUI\\\\nBOS wallet - BOS wallet on NearSocial at BOS hacks: https://near.social/pichtran.near/widget/BOSwallet\\\\n\\\\n### About my team:\\\\n\\\\n- Phuc Tinh: AI engineer; First author of a paper at PACLIC 37 Conference (2023) - Rank C; Co-author of a paper in Neural Computing and Applications journal (Q1, accepted 2024).\\\\n- QuiVo: Blockchain Developer; 3RD Native track at Web3Hackfest with Wedata.\\\\n- Tung Le: Technical Lead.\\\\n- Loc Hoang: Fullstack Developer.\\\\n- Pich Tran: Blockchain Developer.\\\\n\\\\n### **Why We Need the Support**\\\\n\\\\nAs students, we are managing most expenses on our own, but the flight costs present a challenge. This travel stipend would enable us to attend the hackathon and focus fully on building our project and contributing to the NEAR ecosystem, rather than worrying about travel logistics.\\\\n\\\\n### **Conclusion**\\\\n\\\\nWe are excited about the opportunity to participate in the Bangkok hackathon and continue developing on NEAR. Your support would help us cover the necessary travel costs and allow us to concentrate on our project. Thank you for considering our proposal.\\\\n\\\\nBest regards,\\\\n\\\\n@pichtran.near\\\\n\\\\nTeam Nearstack", "linked_proposals": [], "receiver_account": "fastui.near", "requested_sponsor": "neardevdao.near", "proposal_body_version": "V0", "requested_sponsorship_usd_amount": "1000", "requested_sponsorship_paid_in_currency": "USDC"}, "labels": [], "accepted_terms_and_conditions_version": 130872095}
